    description2: `It was still dark when I came to Leningrad. Suburban train stopped not where it always did but two hundred meters away: Finland railway station turned out to be bombed, the platform was blocked. Passengers went out into the street through a small door of the office room - with a crush and screams because the station wise men did not think to open the second door nearby. Bombs hit a restaurant and a cash register. Walls from the side of the platform had collapsed. It happened three days before my arrival. Not far from the station a small wooden house was completely destroyed.`,
