    description2: `On December 4 the area was fiercely shelled. In the evening after "Attention, attention" I stayed in the factory. Otherwise I would be under fire at the tram stop, Germans killed a lot of people.<br> In general, Germans combine it all the time. Good weather, clear skies - a raid of vultures. Bad, snow - artillery shelling. They know that in such weather our planes will not take off, therefore they will fire with impunity.<br> People complain about their legs swelling. They are to blame themselves mostly. I heard this conversation: I ate 5 soups and drank 7 glasses of tea. Well, it's understandable. They cannot resist. They drink more hot water, deceiving their stomach and themselves and burdening the kidneys and bladder. As a result, the legs swell. I spoke in the party committee that it was necessary to organize conversations on the topic of diet. Now with limited nutrition, this is very important. Such a fact: today is December 5, but there are no long queues in the dining room as people ate their cards for the first decade. This means they will starve for the 5 remaining days. Our factory committee, medicine crew does no explanatory work. I set a cruel diet for myself, so I feel great. The stomach works even better now.<br> There is a lull in my factory although I have 4 orders. Either we don't have electricity, either the workers were removed from me. It would be better if we could delay the order. I don't have the details yet!`,
