    description2: `Noon. I filled my lungs with soot. Yesterday I noticed with surprise that I was spitting black, and could not immediately understand what was the matter. Inhaling this soot you will ruin your lungs very soon but... all Leningraders breathe this. I had a glass of water that was still warm and smoked some tobacco. And every time I inhale and exhale, I feel pain in my chest. And most importantly - weakness... The other day I wandered home through Vasilyevsky Island and Petrograd Island. On the square, opposite Dobrolyubov Avenue and Dynamo stadium there were trucks standing in spilled water of broken water pipes, they fell down through the upper crust of ice. Some drivers have not yet lost hope of getting out, they were begging passers-by to help them, or pulling their cars with ropes themselves, standing in the icy water. But these cars are already frozen and they will stay here until spring. Water kept pouring and spreading under a crust of ice. And all the passers-by, including me, had to jump from ice floe to ice floe, climb fences, look for ice bumps in the water in order to bypass the huge expanse of water that filled the entire Bolshoy Prospekt, Pionerskaya Street and the neighborhoods around. Steam was rising from the water. It was freezing. Not finding a way out of it people were calling for help heading to the stuck cars as if they were saving islands.`,
