    description2: `5 am. I wrote down a poem that was just made up during insomnia, in darkness: In this darkness reach for medicines, Accept anything - anything will help In any of the many diseases, Clinging to you as a mob. Then lie down listening to the sounds From the outside world. Few of them remain. Here the clock is ticking. That's all, perhaps. Even the rats all died of hunger. A loudspeaker Is silent as the globe has become so cold That the ether was all frozen around him. But if, apart from cold and darkness, Nothing surrounds you anymore Imagine a map of your native Russia, Become a commander, strike The enemy that we all hate, And your complete victory over him, will shine on you as sun does. And the heart will warm up immediately, Freed from tenacious non-existence. You will touch your chest with a withered hand With a smile: "In the besieged Leningrad With hot faith in a close victory I extended my life for another day!”`,
